    "To achieve underwater object detection, Lau and Lai (2021) focused on the selection and During the detection and recognition of underwater objects, the intensity of underwater light decreases with depth, thereby leading to challenges such as shadows and uneven illumination.",
    "Thus, to address these issues and improve the accuracy of target/object detection and recognition in underwater environments, researchers have proposed several approaches.",
    "For example, Song et al. (2014) used underwater vehicles equipped with visual imaging devices to compensate for targets with varying light intensities.",
